President Muhammadu Buhari has written the National Assembly to reject amendment to the Electoral Act which stipulated re-ordering of the sequence of elections.  Senate President, Bukola Saraki  read the letter of President Muhammadu Buhari rejecting the amendment made to the electoral act  etter dated March 3, 2018  after a closed session that lasted for about 30 minutes. The president in the letter said he rejected the amendment to the electoral act based on three constitutional issues. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The NEWS. Click here to read the full text on the original website.